sections.content: Auxiliary module to provide code api documentation. Once 'backend' data has been generated, customization of the output is using a layer running in the browser. For now, the customization is essentially defined using css through the [Configuration.css](@nav/api/CodeApi.Configuration.css) attribute. Its purpose is to link [Semantic.role](@nav/api/CodeApi.Semantic.role) attribute to display options. For instance, this is the default css file of the [configurationTsTypedoc](@nav/api/CodeApi.configurationTsTypedoc) .
